<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_7e2ead25-7945-4c67-aae9-9d6398c0d690" outputclass="ncc-clause"><sptc>C2P7</sptc><title id="_ef7c8a15-33fa-4928-ac51-45bb63a9d76e">Damage</title><subclause id="_294834ac-9310-4a7e-a7c2-ba2c281a34de" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_7b773404-36ae-4ab4-a4c9-19241c5b80ba">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Damage to sanitary <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/9440_0.8.0.xml#_8310df67-b7b9-4f62-b022-0655a2ae4428" id="_26c86589-c5cb-443d-ab7a-06f21a05a9ff" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drainage systems</xref> from superimposed loads must be avoided. </p></subclause><subclause id="_321df80f-57b1-4141-b5f5-63050ab2eeaa" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_87379230-d493-4efd-8713-9a0cf9a7cec4">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Damage to sanitary <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/9440_0.8.0.xml#_8310df67-b7b9-4f62-b022-0655a2ae4428" id="_8e6492ba-08f5-4477-b3a9-9edd1685809e" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drainage systems</xref> from ground movement must be avoided. </p></subclause><subclause id="_284463ef-afd0-44b2-96a5-e0a32652548f" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_312e0d74-44d2-4c4f-a9b2-d3ef08e027d8">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>Damage to sanitary <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/9440_0.8.0.xml#_8310df67-b7b9-4f62-b022-0655a2ae4428" id="_824813c9-7030-4a5d-b232-ca6f288d5c30" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drainage systems</xref> from root penetration must be avoided. </p></subclause><subclause id="_90b81dd4-36c6-4cb6-9c45-ddfc86ad46dd" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_5cf0d915-17e7-4617-83b8-f4a252bbfa37">SubClause</title><num>4</num><p>Damage to the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_14d60e62-4a3e-42c6-8294-f913062425a8" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator's</xref> sewerage system or any <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1193_0.6.0.xml#_9d2e065b-aa41-45f9-b2f5-4628d8fa28d0" id="_a80e0897-a9ad-41b7-afc8-fa400c5be14c" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">approved disposal system</xref> must be avoided. </p></subclause><subclause id="_0b2c3329-2df4-4163-86fb-9347b0f4d552" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_e0e1fbf6-7660-495b-a811-f7eddac386a0">SubClause</title><num>5</num><p>Damage to siteworks or existing buildings from a sanitary drainage system must be avoided.</p></subclause><callout id="_014b0b03-d1a6-4ba8-8127-9ccaa62973cf"><callout-type ncc-info-type="notes"/><p><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1236_1.0.0.xml#_2f02788f-8757-4689-b36e-e44d96524cc9" id="_aa1638e5-75ef-4835-aebd-a311367fcdcc" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Deemed-to-Satisfy Provisions</xref> for the use of flexible joints in sanitary <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/9440_0.8.0.xml#_8310df67-b7b9-4f62-b022-0655a2ae4428" id="_3b36ed06-9575-4558-9d10-e54bb252a76a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drainage systems</xref> to address ground movement can be found in the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/4251_1.6.0.xml#_fe0463c4-b3a1-49aa-b430-e4f6fb3222d0" id="_5368ec7f-e56b-415c-a382-fbc98351f4a5" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">NSW C2D4</xref>. Other installation methods to avoid damage from superimposed loads, or ground movement to a sanitary <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/9440_0.8.0.xml#_8310df67-b7b9-4f62-b022-0655a2ae4428" id="_f6c7cbd8-323e-4135-935b-46e2375446fd" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drainage system</xref> require the submission of a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1396_4.0.0.xml#_e3f95f1d-e1cc-4ab3-961d-c99a213a1de3" id="_f0a407ec-34d5-4e00-876a-755977fc1bb6" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Performance Solution</xref> to the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1401_0.7.0.xml#_a318c0f3-5635-4ac0-b103-59d798c9f23d" id="_133a51fc-4e77-466a-b6e6-9f2325f7f5e0" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Plumbing</xref> Regulator. </p></callout><callout id="_2ac01adf-c9b2-4063-be47-d77fb5f2e413"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><ul><li>For C2P7(1), superimposed loads that a sanitary <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/9440_0.8.0.xml#_8310df67-b7b9-4f62-b022-0655a2ae4428" id="_b042481b-4c3c-47f0-a564-45ed690fd349" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drainage system</xref> is susceptible to damage from, include building loads and loads arising from building movement or ground movement. </li><li>For C2P7(2), the soil classification of a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1463_0.4.0.xml#_fb3536f6-7ee5-4a29-a4da-402a8e1168dc" id="_b9cb817e-1b1f-493d-a912-17860ee992ba" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">site</xref> should provide an indication of the likelihood for ground movement. </li><li>For C2P7(3), consideration should be given to the location of sanitary <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/9440_0.8.0.xml#_8310df67-b7b9-4f62-b022-0655a2ae4428" id="_072620c3-853d-4e52-94d2-9498db4a3119" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drainage systems</xref> in respect to the existing or proposed surrounding landscape features and implementing appropriate strategies to minimise the likelihood of root penetration. </li><li>For C2P7(5), consideration should be given to factors such as the anticipated type, quality and quantity of waste intended to be discharged. Suitable pre-treatment may be necessary to prevent any potential for damage.</li></ul></callout></clause>